19/06/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Local media reported Monday (19 June) that two unknown gunmen opened fire on a police patrol in Istanbul's Bahcelievler district, wounding two policemen.
Police have launched a massive operation in search of the perpetrators.
On Sunday, three Kurdish militants were reportedly killed in a Turkish security force operation in Tunceli, eastern Turkey, on Sunday (18 June).
The Turkish military's action against the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in the area is still under way.
Also on Sunday, a bomb blast in eastern Turkey damaged 20 cars of a freight train, causing 12 of them to derail.
No injuries were reported.
The authorities are blaming the PKK for the blast.
(CNN Turk - 19/06/06;
Reuters, AFX - 18/06/06)
